projects.name: Home Credit Risk
projects.description: Analyzes and predicts the risk of default for loan applicants using the Home Credit Default Risk dataset. Demonstrates a full-stack data science workflow, including data preprocessing, feature engineering, model training, evaluation, and explainability (SHAP).

projects.name: Fracture Detection
projects.description: Develops a model for automated bone fracture detection using object detection techniques. Utilizes YOLOv4 and Detection Transformers to identify various types of bone fractures from X-ray images.

projects.name: Obesity Prediction
projects.description: Creates a multi-class prediction model to assess obesity risk, focusing on its association with cardiovascular disease. Implements a neural network model and provides a user interface for predictions.

projects.name: Order Appetit
projects.description: A conversational AI system that enables non-technical stakeholders to query MongoDB databases using natural language. Powered by LLMs and a multi-agent architecture, it transforms complex data into actionable insights.

projects.name: Chess Game with RL Environments
projects.description: Creates a smart system that learns to play chess using reinforcement learning methods. Utilizes the PettingZoo environment to train agents in a multi-agent setting.

projects.name: Language Translation
projects.description: Develops a language translation model capable of translating text between multiple languages. Implements sequence-to-sequence models with attention mechanisms.

projects.name: LLMs in Health Science
projects.description: Analyzes breast cancer clinical trial reports using large language models like MedBERT, MedRoBERTa, and Longformer. Aims to assist healthcare professionals in decision-making by evaluating the truthfulness of statements within clinical trial reports.
